ğŸ¯ One-Paragraph Interview-Ready Answer

When a customer performs a card transaction, the POS creates an ISO 8583 authorization or financial request message 
containing card and transaction details. This message is sent to the acquiring bank, routed through the card network 
to the issuing bank, which validates the transaction and sends back a response message with a response code indicating
approval or decline. The response travels back to the POS, and settlement occurs later during batch processing.



